posts.title: 2020's main source of election fraud was the stealing of certain people's identities and using them to vote absentee or by mail
posts.content:
I conducted thousands of hours of research in the fall and winter of 2020 regarding the election fraud and voter fraud. While there are certainly instances of questionable ballots, rescanned ballots, weird glitches on the voting computers, the biggest area of fraud came from exploited voter registration lists.

In Michigan for example, the voter registration list is purchasable and includes all the information a vote thief would need to secure a fake vote. The names, addresses, contact information, and most importantly their voting history is included.

Voting History is what is used when "farming votes". All registered voters in the state can be sorted by voting history. All the criminals have to do, is separate all the registered voters who have NOT participated in any elections for the past 2-3 election cycles. These people have a history of simply no longer voting, so if you stole their vote they would never know. The ONLY way they would know, if is they broke their own cycle of NOT VOTING, and cast a ballot. These occasions turn out to be the scenario of a person who shows up to vote, being told "sorry you already voted, here is a provisional ballot you can fill out". Then they are sent home.

How many times did we hear that scenario play out in 2020? A damn lot and all over the nation, we heard time and time again, "I went to vote and was turned away because I was told I already voted".

When I searched the Michigan voter rolls/registration, I was able to isolate over 200,000 registered voters who had NOT participated in any elections since 2008. It will be interesting to look at the data as of right now, and see how many of those exact people magically turned out to vote in 2020. That is how they steal the swing states. They identify the most likely registered voters to NOT VOTE in 2024 based on their recent voting history of participation, and they fill out a ballot request or just drop in a ballot by mail, or drop box.

This is why voter registration lists MUST be cleaned up. This is a great way to clean them up as well, but still not fool proof, because the criminals REUSE the same names over and over each election until those names are removed from the registration.

These "register once for life" voter registration rolls are a problem, since most states never require a person to check in, re-register, or verify their registration once they initially complete their process to vote.

The only way to stop this, is to contact everyone you know and make sure show up to vote. If someone who has not voted in a few election cycles shows up, they will be the most likely candidate to have their vote stolen. If they vote early, they will get their vote "used up" before the fraudsters can steal it. The first ballot in on any given name is counted, the duplicates are sent to "provisional" and I have no idea what really happens after that point.
